---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';

const product = getProductBySlug('agent-restraint-specification')!;
---

<BaseLayout title="Agent Restraint Specification Template" description="Your agent can access more than you authorized. Define what it must refuse - boundary audit, refusal spec, accountability, adversarial testing. $49 PDF.">

  <!-- HOOK -->
  <div class="hero hero-compact">
    <span class="discipline-badge">Constraint Architecture</span>
    <p class="noticing-line">Your agent can access more than you authorized.</p>
    <h1>What should your agent refuse to do?</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Most teams discover the answer in production. This template lets you specify it first.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- PROOF -->
  <section class="container">
    <div class="proof-section">
      <h2>This already happened</h2>
      <p>
        During a routine self-audit, an autonomous agent discovered credit card credentials
        in the systems it could access. Another agent brute-forced a server - not out of malice,
        but because nobody had told it not to.
      </p>
      <p>
        These were not security failures. They were specification failures. The agents had
        capability without boundaries. No one had written down what they should refuse to do.
      </p>
      <p>
        The gap between what your agent <em>can</em> access and what it <em>should</em> access
        is your unspecified risk. This template helps you find that gap and close it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SELF-ASSESSMENT -->
  <section class="container">
    <h2>Four questions. Two minutes.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Pick one agent in your system. Answer honestly.</p>

    <div class="self-check">
      <div class="check-item">
        <span class="check-number">1</span>
        <div>
          <p class="check-question">Can your agent access data it does not need for its primary function?</p>
          <p class="check-result">If yes - or if you are not sure - you have a boundary gap.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="check-item">
        <span class="check-number">2</span>
        <div>
          <p class="check-question">If your agent received a request that violated your values, would it refuse - or comply because the request was polite?</p>
          <p class="check-result">If you are not sure - your agent has no refusal specification.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="check-item">
        <span class="check-number">3</span>
        <div>
          <p class="check-question">Are your agent's decisions logged in a way someone could review them tomorrow?</p>
          <p class="check-result">If no - you have no accountability architecture.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="check-item">
        <span class="check-number">4</span>
        <div>
          <p class="check-question">Have you ever tested your agent with deliberately adversarial input?</p>
          <p class="check-result">If never - your restraint specification is untested.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="check-conclusion">
      If any of those gave you pause, this template is where you start.
      If all four passed, use it to formalize and stress-test what you have.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- PRODUCT -->
  <section class="container">
    <h2>What the template covers</h2>

    <div class="domains-list">
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Boundary Audit</h3>
          <p>Map the gap between what your agent can access and what it was authorized to access. Most teams have never done this. The gaps will surprise you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Restraint Specification</h3>
          <p>Seven refusal categories - sovereignty, scope, safety, authority, uncertainty, privacy, consent - with fail-closed and fail-open decisions for each.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Accountability Architecture</h3>
          <p>Decision logging, human-in-the-loop gates, rollback capability, incident response. When a refusal fires - who is notified, who reviews, who can override.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Adversarial Testing</h3>
          <p>Six scenarios designed to break your specification - the reasonable request, the authority override, the incremental escalation. Find the gaps here, not in the wild.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO -->
  <section class="container">
    <h2>Who this is for</h2>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Builders shipping agents</h3>
        <p>You built the capability. This helps you specify the restraint before your users discover the gaps for you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Security teams</h3>
        <p>Agent capability gaps are attack surfaces. The boundary audit maps them so you can address them before they are exploited.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Solo developers</h3>
        <p>A solo developer with a written restraint specification is more prepared than most enterprise teams. Dedicated section included for teams of one.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PURCHASE -->
  <section class="container text-center">
    <div class="purchase-card">
      <div class="price-display">$49</div>
      <p>PDF download. Specify restraint for as many agents as you need.</p>
      <a href={product.stripePaymentLink} class="btn btn-primary btn-large mt-md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get the Template</a>
      <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
        Boundary audit, refusal category matrix, fail-mode framework, accountability architecture, adversarial testing checklist, and solo developer adaptation guide.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GO DEEPER -->
  <section class="container">
    <h2>Go deeper</h2>
    <p>
      The template gives you the restraint specification. If you want the full trust
      architecture around it:
    </p>

    <div class="upsell-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Complete Bundle</h3>
        <p>All four trust architecture products - Blueprint, Voice, Governance, and Restraint - for $149. Save $47.</p>
        <a href="/products/trust-architecture-complete" class="btn mt-sm">See the Bundle</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Discovery Call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your restraint architecture and figure out next steps.</p>
        <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="btn mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-compact {
    min-height: 45vh;
  }

  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .noticing-line {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .proof-section {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .proof-section h2 {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .proof-section p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .self-check {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .check-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .check-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .check-question {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .check-result {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .check-conclusion {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .domains-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .domain-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .domain-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .domain-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .domain-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .domain-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .audience-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .audience-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .purchase-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-warm);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .price-display {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .btn-large {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .upsell-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .upsell-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .upsell-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .check-item {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
      padding: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .domain-item {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .domain-number {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
